	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think he wants to simulate *ANY* image as if it was being a game played on the NES. I don't think he cares for the composite artifacts or things like this.
<br />
<br />There could be a generic converter that took an image and attempted to modify it so that it could look like it was generated by a NES, but it would hardly look like a game actually being played.
<br />
<br />It will just look like a poor image conversion, with dithering, color bleed, and so on, things not usually present in an actual game.
<br />
<br />I think it may be funny to do manual convertions of screens from newer systems like the SNES or the Genesis/Mega Drive just to see how the games could have looked if they were made for the NES, but doing it automatically will just look like crap.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


